This fixed code will handle the bug where the `&` and `|` operators are used in the 'bool trigger_pressed' line and it will avoid potential errors when evaluating these operators.

The operators '&' and '|' are short-circuit logical operators. This means that if the left operand is enough to determine the result, the right operand will not be evaluated. This can lead to errors in your application if not handled properly. This fixed code avoids this potential issue by using the logical OR operator '||' instead of the logical AND operator '&&'.

